properties.headline: SCHEDULED ROADWORK - WOOLGOOLGA TO BALLINA Pacific Highway
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
From Monday, there will be five days of work on the Pacific Highway at Pimlico to carry out earthwork and the widening of Kays Road at Pimlico. Motorists can expect traffic control and short stoppages between 7am and 5pm.  

Also from Monday, there will be up to five nights and seven days of work between Woodburn and New Italy to carry out earthwork, paving, drainage work, traffic safety barrier and fauna connectivity pole installation, and to allow access to site. Motorists can expect traffic control, reduced speed limits and short stoppages at times between 6am and 6pm.  

There will be up to four days of work on the Pacific Highway between Devils Pulpit and Mororo from Monday to carry out line marking, drainage work, remove temporary signage and allow access to site to prepare for an upcoming traffic change. Motorists can expect a reduced speed limit between 6am and 6pm while the work is carried out.  

From Monday, there will be six days of work on the Pacific Highway between Mororo and Maclean to carry out landscaping, asphalting, removal of median barriers, and repairs to wire rope safety barriers. Motorists can expect traffic control, short stoppages at times and a reduced speed limit of 40 km/h between 6am and 6pm.  

Further south from Monday, there will be up to six days of work next to the Pacific Highway between Glenugie and Maclean to carry out landscape maintenance, line marking, drainage maintenance, survey and signage work and work in the median at the Maclean interchange. Motorists can expect lane closures, traffic control and a reduced speed limit between 6am and 6pm.  

From Thursday, there will be two days of work next to the Pacific Highway at Broadwater to carry out earthwork. Motorists can expect traffic control and short stoppage at times between 7am and 5pm.
